cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a geometric problem of separating points in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of parameterized complexity and the focus on the number of lines in the solution suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which are relevant to cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.GT (graph theory).
